<TITLE> Durga Puja ends </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 28 (bdnews24.com)The five-day Sharadiya Durga Puja, the biggest religious festival of the Hindus, came to a close on Monday with devotees bidding a tearful goodbye to the Goddess by immersing Her idol. The rituals of the last day of the five-day 'Bijoya Dashami' started with 'Bisharjan Puja' in the morning and ended with Niranjan in the afternoon. The immersion was preceded by rallies with the idols of Durga and her offspringLakshmi, Saraswati, Kartik and Ganesh. In Dhaka, men, women and children joined the rallies singing and dancing to drum beats before the immersion in the Buriganga. The rituals began on Sep 18 with Mahalaya when the devotees invited the Goddess . Durgathe name literally means "Beyond Reach"is worshipped to achieve the spirit of good values by removing the evils inside. The spirit of Durga Puja states that if a person respects and adores a woman as a mother, they will be able to easily get rid of the six cardinal sinssex, anger, greed, infatuation, vanity and envy. She is a youthful, multi-armed deity who successfully battles the mighty buffalo demon 'Mahishashura' that symbolises among other things, the elemental powers of brutish ignorance. The Puja took place in 172 pavilions in the capital, nine more from the previous year, while in over 23,000 pavilions around he country, up 200 from 22,800 stalls last year. bdn
